<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2013-11-13</DATELINE><TITLE>The Lectin ERGIC-53 Goes Viral</TITLE><BODY>The biosynthesis of fusion-competent envelope glycoproteins (GPs) is a crucial step in productive viral infection. In this issue, Klaus et al. (2013) identify the cargo receptor endoplasmic reticulum (ER)-Golgi intermediate compartment 53 kDa protein (ERGIC-53) as a binding partner for viral GPs and a crucial cellular factor required for infectious virus production.&#3;</BODY></TEXT>